#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn4.16"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.16:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.16:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga "
msgstr "2. Rule "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn4.16:0.3"
msgid "16. Pattasutta "
msgstr "16. The Alms Bowls "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.112, sc1
msgctxt "sn4.16:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: samādapeti → samādāpeti (?)
msgctxt "sn4.16:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā pañcannaṃ upādānakkhandhānaṃ upādāya bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandasseti samādapeti samuttejeti sampahaṃseti. "
msgstr "Now at that time the Buddha was educating, encouraging, firing up, and inspiring the mendicants with a Dhamma talk on the topic of the five grasping aggregates. "

#. VAR: aṭṭhiṃ katvā → aṭṭhikatvā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
#. VAR: sabbacetasā → sabbacetaso (si, s1-3, km, pts1) | sabbaṃ cetasā (mr)
msgctxt "sn4.16:1.3"
msgid "Te ca bhikkhū aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi katvā sabbacetasā samannāharitvā ohitasotā dhammaṃ suṇanti. "
msgstr "And those mendicants were paying heed, paying attention, engaging wholeheartedly, and lending an ear. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.250, sc2
msgctxt "sn4.16:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho mārassa pāpimato etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Māra thought, "

msgctxt "sn4.16:2.2"
msgid "“ayaṃ kho samaṇo gotamo pañcannaṃ upādānakkhandhānaṃ upādāya bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandasseti samādapeti samuttejeti sampahaṃseti. "
msgstr "“This ascetic Gotama is educating, encouraging, firing up, and inspiring the mendicants with a Dhamma talk on the topic of the five grasping aggregates. "

msgctxt "sn4.16:2.3"
msgid "Te ca bhikkhū aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi katvā sabbacetasā samannāharitvā ohitasotā dhammaṃ suṇanti. "
msgstr "And the mendicants are paying heed, paying attention, engaging wholeheartedly, and lending an ear. "

msgctxt "sn4.16:2.4"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ yena samaṇo gotamo tenupasaṅkameyyaṃ vicakkhukammāyā”ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I go and pull the wool over their eyes?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn4.16:3.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā pattā abbhokāse nikkhittā honti. "
msgstr "At that time several alms bowls were placed in the open air. "

msgctxt "sn4.16:3.2"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā balībaddavaṇṇaṃ abhinimminitvā yena te pattā tenupasaṅkami. "
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked manifested in the form of an ox and approached those bowls. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.16:3.3"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "One of the mendicants said to another, "

msgctxt "sn4.16:3.4"
msgid "“bhikkhu bhikkhu, eso balībaddo patte bhindeyyā”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicant, mendicant, that ox will break the bowls.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.16:3.5"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When this was said, the Buddha said to that mendicant, "

msgctxt "sn4.16:3.6"
msgid "“na so, bhikkhu, balībaddo. "
msgstr "“Mendicant, that’s no ox. "

msgctxt "sn4.16:3.7"
msgid "Māro eso pāpimā tumhākaṃ vicakkhukammāya āgato”ti. "
msgstr "That’s Māra the Wicked come to pull the wool over your eyes!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.16:3.8"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā “māro ayaṃ pāpimā” iti viditvā māraṃ pāpimantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha, knowing that this was Māra the Wicked, addressed him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn4.16:4.1"
msgid "“Rūpaṃ vedayitaṃ saññā, "
msgstr "“Sights, feeling, and perception, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.16:4.2"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ yañca saṅkhataṃ; "
msgstr "consciousness and what is chosen: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.16:4.3"
msgid "Nesohamasmi netaṃ me, "
msgstr "‘I am not this’ and ‘this is not mine’; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.16:4.4"
msgid "evaṃ tattha virajjati. "
msgstr "that’s how to be free of desire them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn4.16:5.1"
msgid "Evaṃ virattaṃ khemattaṃ, "
msgstr "When you’re detached, secure, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.16:5.2"
msgid "sabbasaṃyojanātigaṃ; "
msgstr "all fetters transcended, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.16:5.3"
msgid "Anvesaṃ sabbaṭṭhānesu, "
msgstr "though Māra and his army chase everywhere "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.16:5.4"
msgid "mārasenāpi nājjhagā”ti. "
msgstr "they never find you.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.251, sc6
msgctxt "sn4.16:6.1"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā … pe … tatthevantaradhāyīti. "
msgstr "Then Māra … vanished right there."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
